file_content.text: I was so close... so close!
I would know who you are and how it is you came to our rescue.
Darth Tormen hired me to deal with Captain Zale Barrows. Him.
I'm working for the Sith.
Your master has my thanks. He will hear of your contribution to our cause.
I am Lord Andreaus Thos. We are what remains of Operations Group One.
I would know who you are and how you came to be in my face.
Who's asking?
Andreaus Thos, leader of Operations Group One. You will address me as "my lord."
You're obviously not with the Republic; I assume the Empire was able to break through the alien filth.
Have our forces been able to free the Dread Masters?
There were some complications with the Esh-kha, but it's been handled.
I took care of it.
They're stretching their legs as we speak.
It's been a complete success.
Good. I will continue my attempts to free these prisoners.
No thanks to you. What are you doing out here?
Wasn't that your job?
The rescue operation's still in progress.
Not that I'm aware of.
At least you've given me a second chance.
Last I heard, things didn't seem to be going well.
I doubt it.
That will change.
We're standing on potential reinforcements numbering in the thousands. I must see to their release.
You tell me; it was your assignment.
Shouldn't you be handling it?
Who are you to question me?
Our groups were split up, decimated and cut off from outside reinforcement. The operation stood no chance of success.
Freeing these prisoners would at least give us a fighting chance.
Unless there's anything else, I've got a Darth waiting for this.
Excuse me, I'm on the job.
You're right. I apologize.
No matter. There are more important matters to be dealt with.
With the Dread Masters no longer in jeopardy, recovering these prisoners is my only concern.
Getting these captives free and in fighting condition is my primary concern.
Carry on with your business, but stay out of my way.
Save your excuses for your commander. I'm sure he'll be real interested.
Tell it to your boss.
You've wasted enough of my time. Finish your business and stay out of my way.
I came for this piece of trash; you just happened to be here.
I didn't come to your rescue.
You have what you want then, begone.
Been thinkin' 'bout this since you dumped me on this rock, Zaley-boy. Got it all worked out how you're gonna go.
Even got in a little practice on your girlfriend.
Kayla! What've you done with her?
Don't worry, saved some of her for you to kiss goodbye.
Aren't you going to do something? You came here for me; what about your bounty?
Never said I had to take you alive.
Still get paid for a corpse.
I'm delivering Barrows in the condition he's in.
Back off, ugly.
We had a deal.
Consider our prior agreement void.
Now we don't.
I'm not helping you torture anyone.
Too bad, sicko.
Fine!
Lucky I still need you.
Thanks. I don't want to know what he had in store for me.
This'll burn a little.
Whatever.
I wouldn't want it to be me.
Least I could do.
Better hope the Sith are feeling less creative.
Don't thank me yet.
If I'm losing credits because of your grudge, I'm taking it out of your hide.
Fine, I better not regret it.
You're already gettin' all you're gonna squeeze outta me.
You crawl into a tomb, Barrows, you risk getting buried.
Me? I'm gonna watch you die.
This's gonna be a real treat.
No, please, no! No!
Corpse is yours. I got all the fun I'm gonna out of it.
You're too kind.
Whatever.
Was that really necessary?
Spend three years in this hole an' ask me again.
Left me enough to clean up.
Looks like it was a lot.
Like you need all of him.
You ain't so bad for a runt. You got style.
You been rubbin' me the wrong way since I met you, but I'll let that slide if you do me a favor.
I figure joinin' up with you's my best shot of gettin' offa this rock. Whatcha say? I'll kill for you.
Fine, but I'll be keeping you on a short leash.
Only if you step in line.
Yeah, yeah, lead the way.
I always wanted my own attack dog.
How could I say no to that?
Real funny.
Fat chance, psycho. I'm done butting heads with you.
Are you kidding me?
Guess you won't be gettin' that stash after all.
You're wrong there.
I'm leavin' on your ship. With or without you. Get me?
I'd rather work with you than against you.
All right, you can come along.
Anybody with the stones to threaten me deserves a fair shake. Come on.
You've got guts. I like that.
Okay, okay, pipe down.
Smart. Real smart.
Let's get the stash I was talkin' about an' blow this joint.
Just get this little twerp outta my sight before I decide to crush him.
Gotcha now, twerp.
How did you--you are good. Nobody shoot! Truce! Look, we can settle our differences, but not right here. I have to stop the Empire.
Drop the blaster, Barrows.
Hands up.
I'm not putting down anything until these Imperial scum stay right where I put them.
Your needs aren't my concern.
We've got you outgunned. If you want a fight, I can give it to you.
Stop them from what?
Explain.
From freeing these prisoners! These monsters!
Maybe you never saw the footage, but I was there when they sacked Coruscant. You know how many civilians died from the bombings alone?
Help us foil their rescue, permanently, and I'll go quietly.
I try not to bite the hand that feeds me.
Sorry, conflict of interest.
Can't blame a guy for trying.
You should have made an offer earlier, Barrows.
The Houk won't let that happen.
You'll go quietly when you're dead.
I've heard enough out of you.
I thought you might say something like that.
Fan out!
You're mine now, runt!
No hurry, no hurry at all!
Whew. Cut it a little close there, Em.
Nice try--you! Huh, I'd kinda hoped the first time I met you it'd be captaining your one-way trip to lockup.
Give up, before you get yourself hurt.
You're trapped.
I've been in better positions, but I like you right where you are at the moment.
Things rarely go the way we want them to.
Sorry to disappoint.
That's deep. You moonlight as a Jedi Master when you're not blowing up orphanages?
Looks like it's the other way around.
You're the one taking a trip.
I'd love to go on a cruise with you, beautiful, but I'm spoken for.
Sorry, chum, don't have time for a trip right now. Work troubles, you know how it is.
Someone's coming.
Rahrr! Lemme in there, you little twerp! You got nowhere to run!
Ahh! Help! Boss help--oh.
And, cue the moron.
Sheesh, this guy's got one answer to everything.
Friend of yours? Hate to disappoint, but even your thick skull won't break though this force field.
What're you standin' around for? Let's blast this place to pieces!
It'd take detonite charges to breach these walls.
Place is too solid.
Then blast the generators!
I don't throw temper tantrums.
Be my guest, crazy.
It ain't a temper tantrum! Blast the generators an' Zale ain't got nowhere left to hide.
How about I start with you, loud mouth?
I don't take your orders.
Yeah? Gimme your best shot. You wanna gut this twerp, go blast the stupid generators.
Soon as this field drops, me an' Zale are gonna get reacquainted.
It's light's out, Zale.
Works for me.
If he's dead when I get back, I'm gonna be real upset.
Don't kill him.
Don't you worry, I plan on keepin' him alive a good long time.
Have fun with that.
I'll be right here, waitin'.
Now'd be a good time to get the power back on!
Em! Em, We've got trouble!
Stopping you isn't in my contract.
Sure, why not?
We had a deal. I kill Zale, you get the stash.
You backin' out? 'Cause I ain't waitin' one more second to break every bone in his little body.
You don't make the decisions here. Shut up and follow my lead.
You'll wait and like it.
Forget you. I'm killin'--I'm... you dirty....
Let's get this over with before he comes to.
If we let him surrender, you can take your time with him.
Kill him afterward.
Better be worth it. All right, Zale. We're in.
Help keep the Imperials, especially that Sith, off of my back while I slice the vault's computer system.
Your deal with me stands.
After what you pulled, I should let him have his way with you.
Hey, I told you to surrender.
Don't be gettin' any cute ideas.
We had a deal. You said I'd get to take my time with him.
I ain't takin' no for an answer.
You've outlived your welcome.
Have it your way. [Attack]
It's no or die, you pick.
Get lost, before I kill you.
I'm gonna pull you apart!
Who said I was stopping you?
Have your fun.
Just makin' sure we're seein' eye to eye.
You know, this'd be going quicker if you hadn't smashed my droid.
Okay, okay, I think I've figured it out.... That ought to take care of it.
Whoa, okay. That's a little weird.
I don't know what exactly a full sample purge is, but I think I've got a lot of blood on my hands.
You did the right thing. The Empire's bad enough without more Sith running around.
Now, if you don't mind, I need to get back to chasing the rest of them out of my galaxy.
You should have come quietly, Zale.
You'll pay for that.
I know what the Sith do to prisoners. Thanks again for the help.
It's gonna take more than a flesh wound to slow me down.
You won't get far.
Guess I'd better get a good head start. Thanks again.
This how you repay a good deed?
Hey, I helped you!
I could have shot you in the head. Thanks again.
Forgettin' somethin', runt.
I see that beauty sleep didn't do you much good.
Shoulda let me kill him. Get up, sissy, or I gotta handle everythin' myself?
Time to make our exit, boys!
You're leaving in lots of little pieces.
You're dead, fella. [Attack]
M3-0B = thought Zale missed excitement // chase + blasters = excitement // M3-0B reduce excitement next iteration
